<!ELEMENT constituency ( #PCDATA ) >

<!-- When the speaker is not an (HC|CD) MP or MEP, he/she will have no contituency. His/her country will be NA. If the speaker is an (HC|CD) MP or MEP, but we no not know his/her country of origin, we will use UNKNOWN -->

<!-- CONSTITUENCY COUNTRY as it was in the very beginning, country meant the country of the person even if he/she didn't belong to the  House, as it is now it is the country which the MP represents, therefore, this element should be required for all MPs, but not for other people. Country is required for ni. And ngo? And what about the special case of Commission, Council... because it is important, how shall we express country for commissioners? In affiliation, because although not elected directly by citizens for a particular role in the EU institutions they represent their country or cover a quote of power for their country -->
<!ATTLIST constituency region CDATA #IMPLIED>
<!-- CONSTITUENCY REGION means any administrative demarcation below country. country #REQUIRED for all corpora, region #IMPLIED for EP and #REQUIRED for CD and HC -->
